==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Histrionical
<hw>His`tri*on"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>histrionicus</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>histrionique</ets>. See <er>Histrion</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or relating to the stage or a stageplayer; befitting
a theatre; theatrical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Affectedly dramatic; insincerely emotional; --
sometimes used in a bad sense.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>His`tri*on"ic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Tainted with false and <qex>histrionic</qex> feeling.</q>
<rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Histrionicism</ent>⟦br⟧
